(After Millay's Blue Beard)

This door you might not open, so I will;
Enter now and witness what faithlessness
You have bought . . . . Here slips what I thought was dulled,
Is sharp as ever and more dangerous.
Finger bones like cleavers, poisonous skulls
Hang off long hooks like tunics of Nessus.
